MEASUREMENTS (
MM
).—N = five males or five females, mean (range). Length of body: males 15.88 (15.00– 16.35), female 18.54 (17.30–19.00); length of fore wing: males 24.59 (23.45–25.75), female 24.66 (23.90–25.35); width of fore wing: males 8.08 (7.70–8.45), female 7.78 (7.40–8.10); length of head: males 2.43 (2.30–2.60), female 2.49 (2.25–2.70); width of head including eyes: males 4.40 (4.25–4.50), female 4.66 (4.55–4.80); width of pronotum including suprahumeral plates: males 6.18 (5.90–6.40), female 6.47 (6.25–6.60); width of mesonotum: males 5.11 (5.00–5.20), female 5.17 (5.00–5.30).
